Dialogue: 0,00:00:16.27,00:00:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunder Rumbles ]
Dialogue: 0,00:00:20.31,00:00:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunderclap ]
Dialogue: 0,00:03:12.07,00:03:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Motor Whirring ]
Dialogue: 0,00:03:15.28,00:03:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Motor Stops ] \N[ Shouting ] \NSee how it's done?
Dialogue: 0,00:03:18.32,00:03:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think I got \Nthe hang of it. \NYou better.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:22.41,00:03:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss'll chew my head off \Nif these cores get messed up. \NDon't worry.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:41.64,00:03:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We're at 26 feet.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:43.89,00:03:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You let Jason \Noperate the drill?
Dialogue: 0,00:03:46.14,00:03:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he can \Nhandle it.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:11.54,00:04:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Motor Slows, Stops ]
Dialogue: 0,00:04:15.96,00:04:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Crunching ]
Dialogue: 0,00:04:18.63,00:04:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Cracking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:04:38.74,00:04:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't do \Nanything!
Dialogue: 0,00:04:46.79,00:04:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Gimme your hand! \NLet go of the drill!
Dialogue: 0,00:04:57.55,00:05:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it, Jack! \NIt's too late!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:13.31,00:05:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not \Ngonna make it!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:24.49,00:05:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:37.42,00:05:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack! \NGimme your hand!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:40.21,00:05:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Yelling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:05:43.26,00:05:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I got you!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:45.22,00:05:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,[ All Shouting ]
Dialogue: 0,00:05:48.85,00:05:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you thinking? \N[ Sighs ]
Dialogue: 0,00:05:52.23,00:05:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's happening? \N- The whole damn shelf \Nis breaking off!
Dialogue: 0,00:05:56.86,00:05:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's \Nwhat's happening!
Dialogue: 0,00:06:02.94,00:06:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Cracking, Rumbling Continue ]
Dialogue: 0,00:06:17.00,00:06:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Jack ] \NWhat we have found \Nlocked in these ice cores...
Dialogue: 0,00:06:19.38,00:06:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is evidence of a cataclysmic \Nclimate shift,
Dialogue: 0,00:06:21.67,00:06:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which occurred around \N10,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:24.22,00:06:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The concentration of these \Nnatural greenhouse gases \Nin the ice cores...
Dialogue: 0,00:06:28.60,00:06:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,indicates that runaway warming \Npushed the planet \Ninto an ice age...
Dialogue: 0,00:06:31.89,00:06:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,which lasted two centuries.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:34.27,00:06:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Speaking \NForeign Language ] \NI'm confused.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:37.73,00:06:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you were talking \Nabout global warming, \Nnot an ice age.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:42.19,00:06:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it is a paradox, \Nbut global warming can trigger \Na cooling trend.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:46.57,00:06:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me explain.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:48.74,00:06:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The northern hemisphere \Nowes its temperate climate \Nto the North Atlantic current.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:53.58,00:06:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Heat from the sun arrives \Nat the equator and is \Ncarried north by the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:57.92,00:07:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But global warming \Nis melting the polar ice caps \Nand disrupting this flow.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:03.76,00:07:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, \Nit will shut down.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:05.88,00:07:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And when that occurs, \Nthere goes \Nour warm climate.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:09.59,00:07:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. \NWhen do you think this \Ncould happen, Professor?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:14.39,00:07:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When? \NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:16.27,00:07:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe in a hundred years. \NMaybe in a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:18.27,00:07:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But what I do know is \Nthat if we do not act soon,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:21.23,00:07:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it is our children \Nand our grandchildren \Nwho will have to pay the price.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:26.82,00:07:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And who's going to pay \Nthe price of the Kyoto Accord?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:29.87,00:07:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It would cost \Nthe world's economy hundreds \Nof billions of dollars.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:33.95,00:07:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,With all due respect, \NMr. Vice President,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:36.45,00:07:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the cost of doing nothing \Ncould be even higher.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:39.58,00:07:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Our climate is fragile.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:42.25,00:07:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,At the rate we're burning \Nfossil fuels and polluting \Nthe environment,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:45.17,00:07:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the ice caps \Nwill soon disappear.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:47.80,00:07:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor, um, Hall,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:51.34,00:07:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,our economy is every bit \Nas fragile as the environment.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:54.64,00:07:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you should keep that \Nin mind before making \Nsensationalist claims.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:58.85,00:08:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the last chunk of ice \Nthat broke off...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:02.48,00:08:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,was about the size \Nof the state of Rhode Island.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:04.90,00:08:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people might call that \Npretty sensational.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:07.78,00:08:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Men Chuckling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:08:11.20,00:08:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,[ People Shouting ] \NStop global warming!
Dialogue: 0,00:08:13.41,00:08:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NI'm here at the Global Warming \NConference in New Delhi,
Dialogue: 0,00:08:16.87,00:08:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,where, if you can believe \Nyour eyes, it's snowing.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:19.16,00:08:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The coldest weather \Non record...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:21.50,00:08:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,has thrown the city \Ninto chaos with numbers \Nof homeless people--
Dialogue: 0,00:08:24.75,00:08:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Taxi! Taxi!
Dialogue: 0,00:08:27.76,00:08:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I enjoyed \Nyour testimony, Professor. \NIt was very spirited.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:31.68,00:08:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you. \NIt's what we're here for, \Nright? Put on a good show?
Dialogue: 0,00:08:35.35,00:08:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite. Uh, \NI was wondering if \NI could talk to you...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:38.81,00:08:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,about your theory \Non abrupt climate shift.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:41.56,00:08:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The name's Rapson. \NTerry Rapson.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:43.77,00:08:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Rapson? \NOf the Hedland Center? \NThat's me.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:47.15,00:08:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I've read your work \Non ocean currents.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:50.11,00:08:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say \Nto a spot of tea? \NAbsolutely.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:52.53,00:08:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If we can hail a cab. \NOh.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:54.70,00:08:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Loud Whistle ]
Dialogue: 0,00:08:57.66,00:09:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,00:09:00.12,00:09:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunder Rumbling ] \N[ Bell Clanging ]
Dialogue: 0,00:09:17.47,00:09:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] Welcome back \Nto Glasgow, Scotland, \N[ Beeping ]
Dialogue: 0,00:09:20.06,00:09:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,where Manchester United \Nleads 3-1 over hometown Celtic, \N[ Man Snoring ]
Dialogue: 0,00:09:23.90,00:09:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in this pivotal champions' \Nleague match.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:26.44,00:09:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We return \Nto the action 63 minutes \Ninto the second half...
Dialogue: 0,00:09:37.78,00:09:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Dennis, NOMAD buoy 4311 \Nis showing a temperature drop...
Dialogue: 0,00:09:41.66,00:09:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of 13 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:44.29,00:09:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hmm? Where is 4311? \N- Well, it's, uh,
Dialogue: 0,00:09:51.42,00:09:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- Georges Bank. \N- Oh, it's rough seas out there. \NMust've knocked it about.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:58.64,00:10:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sheep Bleating ] \N[ Gulls Squawking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:05.31,00:10:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Television Chatter Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:07.31,00:10:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunderclap ] \N[ Announcement In Japanese ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:08.15,00:10:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Announcement Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:18.95,00:10:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Sirens Chirping ] \N- [ Speaking Japanese ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:24.08,00:10:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Cell Phone Ringing ] \N[ Speaking Japanese ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:29.13,00:10:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman On Phone \NSpeaking Japanese ] \N[ Speaking Japanese ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:35.30,00:10:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:10:52.61,00:10:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[ People Screaming ]
Dialogue: 0,00:11:17.68,00:11:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:11:29.60,00:11:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NParker, this is Houston.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:32.11,00:11:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We're seeing \Nsome bad weather \Nover Canaveral.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:35.11,00:11:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't look like \Nyou're coming back \Nthis week.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:37.28,00:11:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chuckles ] \NYour wife's gonna \Ngive me an earful.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:39.36,00:11:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chuckles ] \NRoger that.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:41.99,00:11:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man #2 ] \NHey, come take a look \Nat this storm system.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:44.24,00:11:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's enormous.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:58.22,00:12:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunder Rumbling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:12:03.22,00:12:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunderclap ]
Dialogue: 0,00:12:08.85,00:12:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe \NI'm spending two weeks \Nalone with my mum.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:11.15,00:12:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Be patient with her, all right? \NShe's been looking forward \Nto this holiday for months.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:14.48,00:12:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. \N[ Both Chuckle ]
Dialogue: 0,00:12:16.48,00:12:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you. \NI love you too.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:22.66,00:12:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Hey, hello. \NBye-bye.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:27.08,00:12:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] The cause \Nof this extreme weather \Nremains a mystery,
Dialogue: 0,00:12:29.08,00:12:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,although some meteorologists \Nbelieve sunspots are to blame.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:33.63,00:12:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very odd.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:35.71,00:12:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a buoy here \Nregistering a 13 degree drop \Nin ocean temperature.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:39.84,00:12:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:41.89,00:12:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That buoy malfunctioned \Nthe other day.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:44.35,00:12:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll put a call in, \Nsee if there are any ships \Nnear Georges Bank to get it.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:47.31,00:12:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This buoy isn't \Nin Georges Bank. \NIt's just off Greenland.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:50.60,00:12:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:54.15,00:12:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the odds \Nof two buoys failing?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:56.57,00:12:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Remote.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:03.74,00:13:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Make that three.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:24.72,00:13:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Barking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:13:30.27,00:13:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Roaring ] \N- What's got into them?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:32.73,00:13:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Animals Howling, Calling ] \NI have no idea. \NThey're all worked up today.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:37.15,00:13:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Howling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:13:42.99,00:13:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Phone Ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,00:13:50.70,00:13:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it? \NTerry Rapson here. Sorry \Nto call you so early.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:55.75,00:13:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Professor. \NThat's all right. \NWhat is it?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:57.96,00:14:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we've found \Nsomething extraordinary--
Dialogue: 0,00:14:01.42,00:14:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,extraordinary \Nand disturbing, \Nthat is.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:04.01,00:14:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You recall what you said \Nin New Delhi...
Dialogue: 0,00:14:06.18,00:14:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,about how \Npolar melting might disrupt \Nthe North Atlantic current?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:09.89,00:14:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:11.81,00:14:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:13.69,00:14:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's happening.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:19.52,00:14:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? \NOne of our \NNOMAD buoys...
Dialogue: 0,00:14:22.32,00:14:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,registered a 13 degree drop \Nin surface temperature \Nthe other day.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:26.41,00:14:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I sent you \Nan e-mail. \NHold on.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:31.12,00:14:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,At first we thought \Nit was a malfunction,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:33.75,00:14:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but there are four more \Nacross the North Atlantic \Nshowing the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:38.00,00:14:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Jack ] \NThis is unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:40.42,00:14:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You predicted \Nit would happen.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:43.30,00:14:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but not \Nin our lifetime. \NThis is too fast.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:46.55,00:14:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no forecast models \Nremotely capable \Nof plotting this scenario,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:52.02,00:14:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,except yours.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:53.98,00:14:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My model is a reconstruction \Nof a prehistoric climate shift.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:57.15,00:15:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a forecast model. \NIt's the closest thing \Nwe have.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:01.77,00:15:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing like this \Nhas every happened before.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:05.61,00:15:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,At least not in \Nthe last 10,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:34.77,00:15:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,00:15:36.02,00:15:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't you be monitoring \Nthe weather or something?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:38.85,00:15:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This is L.A. \NWhat weather?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:43.65,00:15:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Motor Running, Faint ] \NWait. \NWhat's that noise?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:46.61,00:15:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What noise?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:49.53,00:15:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Motor Running, Louder ]
Dialogue: 0,00:15:53.74,00:15:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Motor Stops ] \N[ Phone Ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,00:15:57.62,00:16:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sighs ] \NHoney, I'll be \Nright back.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:03.63,00:16:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman ] \NThe coast guard has \Nclosed the beaches...
Dialogue: 0,00:16:05.63,00:16:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,as waves have been too big \Nfor even the most experienced \Nof surfers.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:08.01,00:16:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,L.A. Weather Center. \NIt's Tommy! \NI'm down at the beach!
Dialogue: 0,00:16:10.30,00:16:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in the middle \Nof something. \NWhat do you need?
Dialogue: 0,00:16:12.39,00:16:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There-- Ooh! Uh.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:15.35,00:16:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There's-- There's hail \Nthe size of golf balls \Ncoming down here!
Dialogue: 0,00:16:18.43,00:16:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Tommy Continues, Indistinct ] \N[ Man ] Low pressure system \Nmoving along...
Dialogue: 0,00:16:20.48,00:16:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the California coastline \Nis creating a cyclonic system \Nacross the L.A. basin.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:23.94,00:16:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Phone Ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,00:16:31.11,00:16:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Hello. \NHey, boss, turn on \Nthe Weather Channel.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:33.78,00:16:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we have to issue \Na tornado warning.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:35.79,00:16:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What are \Nyou talking about?
Dialogue: 0,00:16:38.50,00:16:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman ] \NPalmdale and Lancaster \Nare reporting...
Dialogue: 0,00:16:40.50,00:16:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,wind speeds in excess \Nof 70 miles per hour, \NHold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:43.04,00:16:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions that are \Nhighly unusual for California.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:07.86,00:17:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman ] \NWe have live coverage now \Nfrom our Fox 11 chopper.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:11.28,00:17:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you there, Bart? \NUh, yes, I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:13.95,00:17:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,These tornadoes are forming \Nso fast-- What?
Dialogue: 0,00:17:17.12,00:17:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Bart ] \NOh! Oh, my God! \NLisa--
Dialogue: 0,00:17:20.33,00:17:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you getting this on camera? \NThis tornado just came \Nand erased the Hollywood sign.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:24.08,00:17:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hollywood sign is gone. \NIt's just shredded.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:27.80,00:17:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Wind Roaring ] \N[ People Screaming ]
Dialogue: 0,00:17:39.68,00:17:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Lisa ] \NBart, what can you see? \NIs anyone hurt?
Dialogue: 0,00:17:42.06,00:17:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Bart ] \NI wouldn't be surprised. There \Nis so much damage down there.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:44.81,00:17:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are people \Ndown there taking pictures!
Dialogue: 0,00:17:47.73,00:17:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! What the hell \Nare you guys doing!
Dialogue: 0,00:17:49.98,00:17:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Go for cover! \NYou can't stay here! \NGet outta here!
Dialogue: 0,00:17:56.20,00:18:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're seeing are two \Nactual tornadoes striking Los \NAngeles International Airport.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:01.33,00:18:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. Wait. It looks like \Nthey've joined and formed \None large tornado.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:04.58,00:18:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Tommy! \NOh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:10.00,00:18:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NUrge all of our viewers to stay \Naway from the area.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:12.97,00:18:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jeff, where are you? \N- I'm on, uh, Yucca and Vine. \NI'm on my way in now.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:17.93,00:18:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeff, you're on TV! \NYou're right \Nin the middle of it!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:19.93,00:18:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,God. Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:29.52,00:18:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta get \Nout of there, man!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:31.78,00:18:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:36.36,00:18:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Bart ] \NThat bus just got dropped \Non top of that Porsche!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:38.32,00:18:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Line Busy Tone ] \NOh, my God. I hope \Nno one was in that car!
Dialogue: 0,00:18:42.20,00:18:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman ] \NAnd for our national audience \Njust joining us now,
Dialogue: 0,00:18:44.25,00:18:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,we are going live \Nto downtown Los Angeles \Nright now.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:46.46,00:18:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Tommy? \N- If you look over there \Nbehind me, that's a tornado.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:50.67,00:18:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! A twister \Nin Los Angeles.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:53.30,00:18:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one of the many \Ntornadoes that are \Ndestroying our city.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:57.72,00:19:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another one! \NThat's the Los Angeles \Nskyline!
Dialogue: 0,00:19:01.22,00:19:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unbelievable! \NIt's huge! I've never \Nseen anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,00:19:06.02,00:19:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Gasping ]
Dialogue: 0,00:19:16.40,00:19:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,00:19:35.51,00:19:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Rumbling Stops ]
Dialogue: 0,00:19:52.61,00:19:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Wind Howling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:20:02.99,00:20:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Car Alarms Blaring ]
Dialogue: 0,00:20:25.18,00:20:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chattering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:20:28.85,00:20:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. All right. \NListen up, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:31.23,00:20:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up, please. \NWe've got a lot of work to do \Nand we don't have much time.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:35.40,00:20:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's get started, \Nplease. Vorsteen?
Dialogue: 0,00:20:39.61,00:20:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All our grid models \Nare worthless.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:42.24,00:20:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think grid models \Nare gonna be a lot of help here.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:44.49,00:20:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The Canadians are reporting \Ntremendous circulation \Nmoving down from the Arctic.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:48.29,00:20:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In Siberia, there's \Na low pressure system \Nunlike anything we've seen,
Dialogue: 0,00:20:51.67,00:20:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and Australia just saw \Nthe strongest typhoon \Never recorded.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:54.59,00:20:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NHang on. Are you saying that \Nthese things are interconnected?
Dialogue: 0,00:20:57.67,00:20:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Booker ] \NWe have to consider \Nthe possibility.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:59.51,00:21:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The only force strong enough \Nto affect global weather \Nis the sun.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:02.51,00:21:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's NASA have to say? \N- We've already checked. \NSolar output is normal.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:07.43,00:21:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What about \Nthe North Atlantic current? \N[ Vorsteen ] What about it?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:12.56,00:21:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a call last night \Nfrom Professor Rapson \Nat the Hedland Center.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:16.52,00:21:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks the current \Nhas changed.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:18.44,00:21:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Murmuring ]
Dialogue: 0,00:21:20.57,00:21:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Jack. \NHow could that be?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:22.95,00:21:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The current depends upon \Na delicate balance of salt \Nand fresh water.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:25.83,00:21:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- We all know that. \N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:29.33,00:21:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But no one has \Ntaken into account...
Dialogue: 0,00:21:31.41,00:21:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,how much fresh water \Nhas been dumped into the ocean \Nbecause of melting polar ice.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:35.84,00:21:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we've hit \Na critical desalinization point.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:38.59,00:21:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Murmuring ]
Dialogue: 0,00:21:42.38,00:21:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It would explain \Nwhat's driving \Nthis extreme weather.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:44.68,00:21:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hedland had some pretty \Nconvincing data.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:47.64,00:21:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They've asked me to feed it into \Nmy paleoclimate model to track \Nthe next set of events.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:51.68,00:21:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on, Jack. Are you \Nsuggesting these weather \Nanomalies are gonna continue?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:55.52,00:21:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just continue-- \Nget worse.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:02.70,00:22:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we're on the verge \Nof a major climate shift.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:05.28,00:22:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Murmuring ]
Dialogue: 0,00:22:10.20,00:22:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom! \NWhat are you gonna tell \Nthe administration?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:13.46,00:22:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you expect me \Nto tell them?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:15.37,00:22:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The government has \Nto start making long-term \Npreparations now.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:18.25,00:22:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack, all you have is a theory. \NThen give me the mainframe \Nand let me prove it!
Dialogue: 0,00:22:21.21,00:22:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:25.38,00:22:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You have 48 hours.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:27.43,00:22:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sighs ] \NProfessor Hall.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:29.51,00:22:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes? \NI think your theory \Nmay be correct.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:31.97,00:22:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Walk with me.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:33.60,00:22:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a few weeks ago, \NI monitored the strongest \Nhurricane on record.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:37.56,00:22:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The hail, the tornadoes-- \Nit all fits.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:40.23,00:22:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Can the model \Nyou're working on \Nfactor in storm scenarios?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:42.90,00:22:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we haven't had \Nthe time. \NMaybe I can help.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:46.49,00:22:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome aboard. \NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:54.25,00:22:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack. Jack. \NWe got the results.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:06.38,00:23:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Six to eight months. \NThat can't be.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:08.72,00:23:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That time scale \Nisn't in months. \NIt's in weeks.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:16.14,00:23:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, the terrible weather \Nhasn't hit the D.C. area,
Dialogue: 0,00:23:18.06,00:23:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but local residents \Naren't taking any chances,
Dialogue: 0,00:23:20.82,00:23:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as people stock up \Nfor what is already \Nbeing billed...
Dialogue: 0,00:23:23.48,00:23:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,as the worst storm season \Non record.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:26.24,00:23:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You better be sure \Nabout this, Jack. \NMy ass is on the line.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:28.74,00:23:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw the model. \NAnd I hope to God \Nit's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:31.91,00:23:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. \NMr. Vice President. \NTom.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:34.33,00:23:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You know \NProfessor Hall. \NYes, we've met.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:37.12,00:23:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Professor Hall has some \Nnew information I think \Nyou should take a look at.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:40.67,00:23:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We just got these results \Nfrom our simulation model.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:43.55,00:23:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They explain what's causing \Nthe severe weather.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:45.71,00:23:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll look at this later. \NI have a meeting with \Nthe director of FEMA now.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:49.34,00:23:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very urgent, sir. \NOur climate \Nis changing violently.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:52.22,00:23:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to happen \Nover the next six \Nto eight weeks.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:54.89,00:23:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you said this \Nwouldn't happen for another \Nhundred years or so.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:57.73,00:24:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wrong. \NWell, suppose \Nyou're wrong this time.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:00.35,00:24:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish that I were, but I'm sure \Nthat you're aware of what's \Nhappening all around the world.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:04.36,00:24:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We're making all the necessary \Npreparations for this storm. \NWhat more do you expect?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:07.95,00:24:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to start \Nthinking about large scale \Nevacuations right now,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:11.95,00:24:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,especially in \Nthe northern states.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:13.99,00:24:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Evacuations? \NYes.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:16.12,00:24:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you lost \Nyour mind, Hall? \NI have to go.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:20.00,00:24:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Vice President, \Nif we don't act now, \Nit's going to be too late.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:28.84,00:24:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:33.60,00:24:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NIt's been 24 hours now since \Nthe snow started falling...
Dialogue: 0,00:24:36.97,00:24:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,across the British Isles \Nand over northern Europe,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:38.98,00:24:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and it shows no signs \Nof letting up.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:41.15,00:24:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No. No, no, no. \NYou gotta stop worrying. \NNo.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:43.81,00:24:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine. We got plenty \Nof supplies with us. \NWe're just snowed in.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:47.94,00:24:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. No, it's all right. \NIt's all right.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:50.99,00:24:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You stay \Nwhere you are, okay? \NI'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:52.99,00:24:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I love you too. \NOkay. Bye. \N[ Sighs ]
Dialogue: 0,00:24:56.87,00:25:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey. How's Jeanette? \N- Oh, fine.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:01.50,00:25:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ferry just landed. \NMust be nice in Spain. \NI wish I was there.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:06.59,00:25:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[ TV: Reporter ] \NThe search and rescue team has \Nbeen deployed by helicopter...
Dialogue: 0,00:25:09.26,00:25:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to airlift \Nthe royal family to safety.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:12.18,00:25:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You think \Nthey'll come get us, \Nsince we got snowed in?
Dialogue: 0,00:25:14.35,00:25:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Not likely.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:16.85,00:25:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, \Nwe got our own genny,
Dialogue: 0,00:25:18.85,00:25:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,enough tea and biscuits \Nto sink a ship.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:21.39,00:25:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we'll be fine. \NAs long as the loo \Ndoesn't back up again.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:25.02,00:25:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[ All Chuckle ]
Dialogue: 0,00:25:29.86,00:25:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In Ireland, those remaining \Nin Belfast and Banbridge \Nhave been urged to evacuate...
Dialogue: 0,00:25:34.20,00:25:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to Dublin as soon \Nas possible.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:37.45,00:25:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The north continues \Nto receive the worst \Nof the storm--
Dialogue: 0,00:25:41.58,00:25:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Helicopter Approaching ]
Dialogue: 0,00:25:46.09,00:25:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NWe've got zero visibility. \NMaintain heading and speed.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:49.42,00:25:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Man #2 ] \NWhat's our heading? \N- Zero, three, five, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:51.84,00:25:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Approximately 40 kilometers \Nfrom Balmoral Castle.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:55.09,00:25:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NWe've lost visual contact \Nwith you.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:21.25,00:26:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This gauge here \Ncan't be right.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:23.29,00:26:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man #3 ] \NWind speed has dropped to zero.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:25.33,00:26:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We have vertical walls \Nof cirrus cloud formations.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:27.92,00:26:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NWhat the hell \Nis going on?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:29.46,00:26:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Bloody fuel lines \Nare starting to freeze!
Dialogue: 0,00:26:35.93,00:26:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Men Shouting ]
Dialogue: 0,00:26:42.64,00:26:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Port engine pressure's dropping! \NThe rotor R.P.M. is dropping!
Dialogue: 0,00:26:46.65,00:26:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got a flame-out \Non the starboard side as well!
Dialogue: 0,00:26:53.28,00:26:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare \Nfor crash landing!
Dialogue: 0,00:26:56.95,00:26:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Select emergency fuel!
Dialogue: 0,00:26:59.99,00:27:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, \Nyou bastard!
Dialogue: 0,00:27:02.70,00:27:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,00:27:18.39,00:27:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Breathing Heavily ]
Dialogue: 0,00:27:27.85,00:27:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Rapson ] \NWhat I'm about to tell you \Nis supposed to be confidential.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:30.81,00:27:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Several hours ago, \Nthree helicopters went down \Nover Scotland.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:34.74,00:27:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They crashed because the fuel \Nin their lines froze.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:38.32,00:27:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,At what temperature does--
Dialogue: 0,00:27:40.28,00:27:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Rapson On Speaker ] \NNegative 150 degrees Fahrenheit. \NWe had to look it up.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:45.50,00:27:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The temperature dropped \Nphenomenally fast.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:47.83,00:27:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,On the ground, people froze \Nbefore they could \Nget out of their cars.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:51.21,00:27:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- Get me a satellite picture \Nof Scotland two hours ago. \N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:55.34,00:27:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got mountains of data \Nbut nowhere near enough \Ncomputer power to analyze it.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:59.84,00:28:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- Can you help us? \N- Send us what you've got, \Nand we'll do our best.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:03.26,00:28:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Rapson ] \NThanks, Jack. Bye for now.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:06.89,00:28:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Scotland at the time \Nthe temperature dropped.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:12.69,00:28:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Frank ] \NThis thing looks \Njust like a hurricane.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:15.53,00:28:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Janet ] \NOnly hurricanes don't form \Nover land.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:19.57,00:28:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mob scene here \Nat Grand Central Station.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:22.03,00:28:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Over half the platforms \Nare flooded,
Dialogue: 0,00:28:24.33,00:28:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and service has been \Nsuspended on all trains.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:27.25,00:28:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,With planes still grounded \Nand trains now out of service, \Nthat's bad news--
Dialogue: 0,00:28:31.83,00:28:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Victor's coming to pick me up. \NDo you guys want a ride \Nto the train station?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:35.55,00:28:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Stranded \Nsince this morning. \NNot anymore.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:38.76,00:28:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In Nova Scotia earlier, \Nthe ocean rose by 25 feet \Nin a matter of seconds.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:43.26,00:28:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What we have feared \Nfor the past few days \Nhas indeed happened.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:47.60,00:28:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The cold front moving down \Nfrom the Arctic...
Dialogue: 0,00:28:49.85,00:28:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,has created an enormous \Nstorm system in Canada,
Dialogue: 0,00:28:52.77,00:28:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,which, incredible as it sounds, \Nlooks like a tropical hurricane.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:56.19,00:28:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I gotta go pick up \Nmy little brother. \NDo you guys want a ride?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:59.78,00:29:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he? \NHe's in a boarding school \Nin Philadelphia.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:03.12,00:29:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If this system moves south, \Nwe could see a wind-driven \Nstorm surge...
Dialogue: 0,00:29:08.04,00:29:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that could threaten \Nthe entire Eastern Seaboard.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:11.37,00:29:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Bye. Victor's stuck \Nin traffic on Fifth Avenue.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:15.54,00:29:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be easier \Nto head out of town \Nif we meet him over there.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:18.63,00:29:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. \NYou mean walk? \NNo, not in this.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:23.01,00:29:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunder Rumbling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:29:25.60,00:29:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We should take \Nthe stairs.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:28.06,00:29:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We're on the top floor.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:32.94,00:29:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we're walkin'.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:37.23,00:29:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunderclap ]
Dialogue: 0,00:29:39.53,00:29:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Horns Honking, \NPeople Shouting ]
Dialogue: 0,00:29:47.16,00:29:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should just stay here. \NI think the young lady \Nis right, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:51.58,00:29:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No. We need to get home.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:54.54,00:29:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! \N[ Shouting Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:30:07.22,00:30:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Goats Bleating ]
Dialogue: 0,00:30:12.98,00:30:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Growls ]
Dialogue: 0,00:30:19.19,00:30:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Cesar, come here.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:21.40,00:30:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:28.24,00:30:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The wolves! \NThey're gone!
Dialogue: 0,00:30:31.20,00:30:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man On News ] \NJust to give you an idea \Nof the situation,
Dialogue: 0,00:30:33.87,00:30:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which seems to be becoming \Nworse with each passing minute,
Dialogue: 0,00:30:37.04,00:30:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,at the moment, we have flooding \Nin most parts of the island.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:41.13,00:30:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got traffic snarl-ups \Nbecause the electricity \Nis now out...
Dialogue: 0,00:30:44.17,00:30:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to almost every part \Nof Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:47.14,00:30:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No traffic signals, \Ncar accidents-- at least 200--
Dialogue: 0,00:30:50.72,00:30:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and Lower Manhattan, we've been \Ntold, is virtually inaccessible.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:54.94,00:30:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NNo one is to be on the streets. \NPlease go inside.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:59.52,00:31:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Excited Chattering ] \NSir, just calm down.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:04.78,00:31:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Public library's right up here. \NMake your way up there. \NYou can stay warm and dry.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:07.66,00:31:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, guys. \NThis way.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:10.33,00:31:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. \NYour bad.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:12.74,00:31:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Goddamn $1,500 \Nwaterproof raincoat!
Dialogue: 0,00:31:15.75,00:31:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Please shut up, man.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:17.71,00:31:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There must be rats \Neverywhere. \NThat's 'cause it's New York.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:20.59,00:31:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hey! \NOpen up, big poppa!
Dialogue: 0,00:31:24.72,00:31:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's out of service. \NIt's out of service!
Dialogue: 0,00:31:28.47,00:31:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no. I'll give you \N$100 to put it in service. \NYou don't have to do that.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:31.43,00:31:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no. Really, $200. \NI won't have it. \NI won't have it.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:34.93,00:31:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, I love buses. \NThis is just so much fun.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:37.77,00:31:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shouting ] \NHello?
Dialogue: 0,00:31:40.36,00:31:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't reach my driver. \NI lost the signal.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:43.07,00:31:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This is insane. \NWe should just go back \Nto your apartment.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:45.78,00:31:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Brian ] \NYeah. I vote for that.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:47.78,00:31:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Are you kidding? \NWe have to get higher!
Dialogue: 0,00:31:50.45,00:31:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. \NUp to the library.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:53.29,00:31:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Thunderclap ]
Dialogue: 0,00:32:18.06,00:32:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shouting Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:32:22.15,00:32:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Child Screams ] \N- [ Thunderclap ]
Dialogue: 0,00:32:42.21,00:32:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man On News ] \NThere is a wall of water \Ncoming towards New York City!
Dialogue: 0,00:32:45.55,00:32:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody--
Dialogue: 0,00:32:48.76,00:32:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shouting, Screaming ]
Dialogue: 0,00:32:55.06,00:32:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Woman Screams ] \N- [ Shouting Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:33:33.43,00:33:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my--
Dialogue: 0,00:33:41.52,00:33:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Laura!
Dialogue: 0,00:33:48.53,00:33:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Laura!
Dialogue: 0,00:33:51.03,00:33:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No! No! \NNo, Sam! Sam, no!
Dialogue: 0,00:33:52.95,00:33:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Laura! Laura! Laura! \NCome on! \N[ Gasps ]
Dialogue: 0,00:33:57.20,00:34:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Come! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,00:34:01.79,00:34:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sam! \N- Go!
Dialogue: 0,00:34:22.85,00:34:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Dog Barking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:34:41.29,00:34:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Here he is.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:45.33,00:34:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack, were you able \Nto re-create the thermal cycle?
Dialogue: 0,00:34:49.25,00:34:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The storm's rotation \Nis pulling super-cooled air \Ndown from the upper troposphere.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:57.59,00:35:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But shouldn't the air warm up \Nbefore it reaches ground level?
Dialogue: 0,00:35:01.64,00:35:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It should, but it doesn't. \NThe air's descending \Ntoo rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:06.23,00:35:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this \Nan isolated incident?
Dialogue: 0,00:35:11.82,00:35:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid not.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:13.86,00:35:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We've located two other \Nsupercells in addition \Nto the one over Scotland.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:17.66,00:35:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one over Northern Canada \Nand another one over Siberia.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:21.99,00:35:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And do we know \Ntheir projected path?
Dialogue: 0,00:35:25.62,00:35:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Our previous estimates \Nof six to eight weeks \Nweren't even close.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:30.21,00:35:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This one storm is going \Nto change the face \Nof our planet.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:33.92,00:35:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a projection \Nof 24 hours out.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:42.01,00:35:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is 48 hours out.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:46.89,00:35:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And in seven to 10 days.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:52.73,00:35:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When this storm is over, \Nwe'll be in a new ice age.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:01.74,00:36:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,My God.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:22.05,00:36:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor, it's time \Nyou got out of there.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:27.81,00:36:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid that time \Nhas come and gone, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:36.07,00:36:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do?
Dialogue: 0,00:36:41.66,00:36:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Save as many as you can.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:44.28,00:36:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Feedback On Line ]
Dialogue: 0,00:36:49.29,00:36:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Disconnect Signal ]
Dialogue: 0,00:36:55.05,00:36:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Phone Ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,00:36:59.26,00:37:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack. Something's \Nhappened in New York.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:13.44,00:37:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No. The power is out. \NI've been in here all day.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:16.73,00:37:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Officer ] \NWho needs help? \NOver here. Over here.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:19.99,00:37:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Indistinct Shouting ] \NHi.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:22.49,00:37:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man ] \NHello. \N[ Dog Whimpering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:37:26.53,00:37:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,00:37:29.20,00:37:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the last one. \NEnjoy it. Greedy.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:34.29,00:37:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Operator ] \NAll circuits are busy.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:36.84,00:37:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Dialing Phone ]
Dialogue: 0,00:37:38.67,00:37:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you reach \Nyour little brother yet?
Dialogue: 0,00:37:41.42,00:37:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No. There's still no service. \NDamn cell phones.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:49.52,00:37:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- Excuse me. \N- Yes?
Dialogue: 0,00:37:51.64,00:37:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there any pay phones \Non the upper floors? \NNo. No.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:54.48,00:37:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are some \Non the mezzanine. \NGreat.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:57.32,00:37:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- But I think it's underwater. \N- Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,00:37:59.78,00:38:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The power's out. \NOlder pay phones draw their \Npower directly from the line.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:03.78,00:38:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman On P.A., Indistinct ]
Dialogue: 0,00:38:06.41,00:38:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God. I've been trying \Nto reach Sam.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:10.16,00:38:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So have I. \NI kept trying to call you, \Nbut I couldn't get through.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:14.46,00:38:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a madhouse \Naround here. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:22.01,00:38:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:27.30,00:38:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. Oh.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:32.18,00:38:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Dial Tone ] \N- It works.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:35.81,00:38:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack? Sam's on the phone. \NLine four.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:40.40,00:38:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sam? \N- Dad!
Dialogue: 0,00:38:43.03,00:38:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you? \NAre you all right? \NWe're at the public library.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:46.11,00:38:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sam, it's Mom. \NI'm so happy you're okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:50.12,00:38:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, can you call \NLaura and Brian's parents \Nand tell them we're all right?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:54.87,00:38:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Of course.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:57.21,00:39:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sam, what's that noise? \N- Sam? Sam?
Dialogue: 0,00:39:01.00,00:39:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Gasping ] \NWhat is going on out there, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,00:39:06.13,00:39:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sam? Sam, listen to me. \NListen very carefully.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:10.31,00:39:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget what I said \Nabout trying to head south.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:13.02,00:39:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too late for that. \NThe storm is just gonna \Nget worse.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:16.06,00:39:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gonna turn into \Na massive blizzard with an eye \Nin the center, like a hurricane.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:20.23,00:39:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- Uh-huh. \N- The air is gonna be so cold,
Dialogue: 0,00:39:23.03,00:39:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you could freeze to death \Nin seconds.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:27.95,00:39:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sam? \N- What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,00:39:31.33,00:39:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to me, son. \NDo not go outside.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:34.58,00:39:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Just burn whatever you can \Nto stay warm and try \Nto wait it out.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:38.37,00:39:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I will come for you. \NDo you understand me? \NI will come for you.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:41.80,00:39:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shivering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:39:44.30,00:39:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sam! Sam, come back!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:48.30,00:39:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Jack ] \NSam? Sam, did you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,00:39:51.55,00:39:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,00:40:13.03,00:40:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Gasping ]
Dialogue: 0,00:40:16.37,00:40:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shivering, Panting ]
Dialogue: 0,00:40:18.87,00:40:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sobbing ] \NI thought you drowned.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:26.71,00:40:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's find some \Ndry clothes for you. \NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:36.35,00:40:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did you store \Nthe arctic gear?
Dialogue: 0,00:40:39.31,00:40:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't make it \Nto New York, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:41.73,00:40:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I've walked that far \Nbefore in the snow.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:44.65,00:40:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not the same. \NJack, this is not the same!
Dialogue: 0,00:40:49.24,00:40:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy, tell him.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:52.91,00:40:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to do this.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:57.25,00:40:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:05.25,00:41:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Frank told me about Sam.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:07.84,00:41:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not gonna try \Nto talk you out of going,
Dialogue: 0,00:41:10.26,00:41:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's something \NI need for you to do first.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:13.14,00:41:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to explain your results \Nto the administration.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:15.93,00:41:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I already tried that. \NI know this time \Nwill be different.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:18.06,00:41:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're gonna brief \Nthe president directly.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:23.52,00:41:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Officer ] \NIs that the last of it?
Dialogue: 0,00:41:25.52,00:41:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Laura ] \NYeah. Pretty much. \NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:28.19,00:41:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We also found this radio, \Nbut I don't think it works.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:30.78,00:41:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see it.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:33.53,00:41:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Barking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:41:38.58,00:41:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha, be quiet!
Dialogue: 0,00:41:41.21,00:41:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You ain't even supposed \Nto be in here anyway.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:44.88,00:41:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Barking Continues ] \N- [ Loud Rumbling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:41:54.89,00:41:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Rumbling Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:42:28.29,00:42:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Barking Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,00:42:39.43,00:42:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, guys.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:47.73,00:42:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:59.37,00:43:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Glass Shattering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:43:12.38,00:43:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic rule of storms \Nis that they continue...
Dialogue: 0,00:43:15.26,00:43:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,until the imbalance \Nthat created them is corrected.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:18.43,00:43:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, we're talking \Nabout a global realignment.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:22.18,00:43:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The superstorm will \Nlast seven to 10 days.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:25.60,00:43:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's over, ice and snow \Nwill cover the entire \NNorthern Hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:30.82,00:43:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The ice and snow \Nwill reflect sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:34.40,00:43:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The earth's atmosphere \Nwill restabilize...
Dialogue: 0,00:43:36.61,00:43:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but with an average \Ntemperature close to that \Nof the last ice age.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:41.37,00:43:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do about this?
Dialogue: 0,00:43:43.33,00:43:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sighs ] \NHead as far south as possible.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:46.83,00:43:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not amusing, \NProfessor.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:49.13,00:43:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you suggest \Nthey go?
Dialogue: 0,00:43:51.84,00:43:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The farther south they go, \Nthe safer they'll be.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:54.71,00:43:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Texas. Parts of Florida \Nthat aren't flooded. \NMexico would be best.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:58.89,00:44:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mexico? Maybe \Nyou should stick to science \Nand leave policy to us.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:03.06,00:44:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we tried that approach. \NYou didn't want to hear \Nabout the science...
Dialogue: 0,00:44:06.35,00:44:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,when it could \Nhave made a difference.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:09.81,00:44:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly are you \Nproposing, Professor?
Dialogue: 0,00:44:18.95,00:44:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Evacuate everyone \Nsouth of that line.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:28.08,00:44:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the people \Nin the north?
Dialogue: 0,00:44:34.34,00:44:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid \Nit's too late for them.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:37.13,00:44:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If they go outside, \Nthe storm will kill them.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:44.56,00:44:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point,
Dialogue: 0,00:44:47.23,00:44:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,their best chance \Nis to stay inside,
Dialogue: 0,00:44:50.48,00:44:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,try to ride it out,
Dialogue: 0,00:44:53.86,00:44:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,pray.
Dialogue: 0,00:44:59.95,00:45:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think he'll do?
Dialogue: 0,00:45:02.70,00:45:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:04.91,00:45:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:07.87,00:45:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And good luck.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:09.87,00:45:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You too.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:13.67,00:45:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all gonna need it.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:18.42,00:45:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Wind Howling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:45:23.59,00:45:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Generator Chugging ]
Dialogue: 0,00:45:35.48,00:45:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, mates, but we're \Njust about out of petrol.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:42.32,00:45:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, is there any chance...
Dialogue: 0,00:45:46.03,00:45:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that it will run... on this?
Dialogue: 0,00:45:50.20,00:45:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chuckles ] \NAre you mad?
Dialogue: 0,00:45:53.04,00:45:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a 12-year-old scotch.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:03.05,00:46:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,00:46:17.27,00:46:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen. To England.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:22.86,00:46:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,To mankind.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:26.28,00:46:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,To Manchester United.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:28.53,00:46:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[ All Laughing ]
Dialogue: 0,00:46:53.52,00:46:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Buddha. Come on. \NDo your business.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:57.06,00:46:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Look. There's nobody around.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:59.98,00:47:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Buddha Whimpering ] \NOkay. You know what? \NI'll turn around. I won't look.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:03.15,00:47:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise. \N[ Barking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:47:05.74,00:47:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Barking Continues ] \NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:15.75,00:47:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, man. \NThere's people out there. \NI was walking my dog.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:19.42,00:47:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There's hundreds of 'em. \NThey're walkin' on the snow.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:26.97,00:47:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chattering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:47:31.26,00:47:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Officer ] \NWhere are they all going?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:33.27,00:47:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They're gettin' \Nout of the city \Nbefore it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:38.90,00:47:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Wind Howling ]
Dialogue: 0,00:48:07.22,00:48:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:09.22,00:48:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to be \Non a bus heading south.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:12.72,00:48:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been watching \Nyour back for 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:15.56,00:48:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I'd let you \Ngo alone?
Dialogue: 0,00:48:18.06,00:48:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All these years, I thought \NI was watching your back.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:21.02,00:48:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are the keys? \NIn the truck.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:24.73,00:48:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you think \Nyou're going?
Dialogue: 0,00:48:27.24,00:48:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither one of you \Nknows how to navigate \Nworth a damn.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:30.11,00:48:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Without me, you'll \Nend up in Cleveland.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:34.24,00:48:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try to give you \Nupdates on the storm \Nas it heads your way.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:37.75,00:48:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:40.50,00:48:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Engine Starts ]
Dialogue: 0,00:48:53.55,00:48:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman Reporting ] \NBreaking news from \Nthe U.S.-Mexico border.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:56.60,00:49:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Just half an hour ago, \NMexican officials \Nclosed the border...
Dialogue: 0,00:49:00.10,00:49:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in the light \Nof so many U.S. refugees \Nwho are fleeing south...
Dialogue: 0,00:49:04.07,00:49:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in the wake \Nof the approaching storm.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:06.44,00:49:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,These people came here \Nin anticipation of crossing \Ninto Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:10.07,00:49:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, they've been met \Nwith closed gates--
Dialogue: 0,00:49:12.99,00:49:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:15.03,00:49:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this fireplace \Nprobably hasn't been used \Nin about a hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:22.58,00:49:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:29.97,00:49:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are you doing? \N- What do you think \Nwe were gonna burn?
Dialogue: 0,00:49:33.55,00:49:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't burn books. \NNo. Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 0,00:49:37.14,00:49:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanna freeze to death?
Dialogue: 0,00:49:41.81,00:49:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go get some more. \NI'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:45.90,00:49:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going with them.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:49.32,00:49:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Do you have \Na cafeteria or a lunchroom?
Dialogue: 0,00:49:52.61,00:49:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Just an employees' lounge \Nwith a few vending machines.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:55.16,00:49:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Buddha Barking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:50:02.92,00:50:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not gonna last very long \Non M&M's and potato chips.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:05.58,00:50:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the garbage cans? \NThere's always somethin' \Nto eat in the garbage.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:09.46,00:50:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Buddha Whimpering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:50:19.47,00:50:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Gasps ] \NAre you all right?
Dialogue: 0,00:50:22.27,00:50:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'm fine. I just \Ncut my leg the other day.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:25.40,00:50:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Radio Static ]
Dialogue: 0,00:50:28.82,00:50:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get a signal?
Dialogue: 0,00:50:31.40,00:50:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. For a minute. \NAnd?
Dialogue: 0,00:50:38.45,00:50:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, this storm is everywhere. \NIt's hit the entire \NNorthern Hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:43.21,00:50:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Europe is buried \Nunder 15 feet of snow.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:46.92,00:50:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And they say it's gonna \Nget just as bad here.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:49.38,00:50:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I don't think \Nyour dad's gonna make it.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:56.30,00:50:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No. He'll make it.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:02.52,00:51:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll make it.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:08.36,00:51:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man On News ] \NThe White House has ordered...
Dialogue: 0,00:51:10.40,00:51:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the following national disaster \Nalert for all northern states:
Dialogue: 0,00:51:14.20,00:51:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Continued exposure \Nto the approaching storm \Nis deadly.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:17.32,00:51:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Remain indoors and take \Nall measures to stay warm,
Dialogue: 0,00:51:19.66,00:51:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,burning any fuel sources \Nuntil the storm is over.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:23.08,00:51:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Roads are impassable \Nacross New York State...
Dialogue: 0,00:51:25.46,00:51:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and as far south \Nas Pennsylvania. \NWhere are we?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:28.21,00:51:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man On News Continues, \NIndistinct ]
Dialogue: 0,00:51:30.84,00:51:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like we're \Njust north of Philadelphia.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:34.22,00:51:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man On News ] \NRescue workers say \Nthey have no idea--
Dialogue: 0,00:51:37.34,00:51:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,00:51:41.72,00:51:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys okay?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:44.48,00:51:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. \NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:52.36,00:51:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- Once again, roads across \Nthe northern states... \N- Sorry, boss.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:55.78,00:52:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,are impassable. \NUnpack the snowshoes. \NWe're walking from here.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:02.24,00:52:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, men. \NLet's get up and get going.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:05.54,00:52:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We've only made it to Brooklyn. \NMaybe we should just turn back.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:10.88,00:52:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What for? Half the city's \Nfrozen underwater.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:13.55,00:52:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to go back to. \NIt's time to get up. \NKeep moving.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:16.38,00:52:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We should've stayed \Nin the library. \NCome on, men.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:20.05,00:52:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, guys. \NLet's get moving.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:32.27,00:52:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:51.96,00:52:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing? \NInsulatin'.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:55.92,00:52:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Newspaper's best, \Nbut this'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:58.55,00:53:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you spend \Nsome years on the streets, \Nand you learn how to keep warm.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:02.60,00:53:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:08.98,00:53:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:50.35,00:53:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Grunting, Screaming ]
Dialogue: 0,00:54:06.53,00:54:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Groaning, Whimpering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:54:15.42,00:54:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Jack ] \NFrank!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:17.46,00:54:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right? \NI'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:22.59,00:54:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Just dropped in \Nto do a little shopping.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:25.34,00:54:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I gotta lose this sled.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:45.03,00:54:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on! \NWe'll pull you up!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:49.54,00:54:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Jason! You gotta \Nsupport Frank's weight!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:52.87,00:54:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! I'll try!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:57.84,00:54:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Grunting ]
Dialogue: 0,00:55:01.71,00:55:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! I think \NI have his weight now!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:04.84,00:55:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming to you!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:13.23,00:55:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Glass Cracking ]
Dialogue: 0,00:55:15.60,00:55:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Grunting, Whimpering ]
Dialogue: 0,00:55:18.56,00:55:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The glass is breaking!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:23.57,00:55:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Too much weight!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:29.37,00:55:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not gonna hold.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:40.46,00:55:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No! No!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:42.13,00:55:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Frank! \NI can get you out!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:47.13,00:55:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Jack ] \NDon't do it!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:49.34,00:55:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- No! Frank! Don't! \N- Frank, no!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:53.31,00:55:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Frank!
Dialogue: 0,00:56:37.43,00:56:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Radio: \NChatter, Indistinct ]
Dialogue: 0,00:56:39.94,00:56:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Get this convoy \Nmoving now.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:44.36,00:56:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Whispering ] \NI know. I know.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:47.32,00:56:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. President. \NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:50.11,00:56:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, sir. \NWe can't wait any longer.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:53.12,00:56:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the last ones.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:55.54,00:56:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:12.80,00:57:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Pilot ] \NMexicali Control, \Nthis is Delta 2-6.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:15.51,00:57:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We're carrying an urgent message \Nfor high command.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:18.48,00:57:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Request priority \Non landing zone one.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:20.60,00:57:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Chattering, Shouting ] \N[ Radio Chatter Continues, \NIndistinct ]
Dialogue: 0,00:57:28.86,00:57:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:30.99,00:57:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Corporal. \NCarry on.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:46.63,00:57:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Madam Secretary?
Dialogue: 0,00:57:58.02,00:58:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Raymond.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:00.39,00:58:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The president's motorcade \Ngot caught in the storm.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:07.77,00:58:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't make it.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:15.53,00:58:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,She wouldn't \Nwake up this morning.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:17.87,00:58:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I-- I mean, last night \Nshe only had a fever. \NI don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:21.29,00:58:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,God, she's awfully pale.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:23.25,00:58:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, guys, look. \Nnone of us has had anything \Nreal to eat in days.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:26.29,00:58:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Jeremy ] I'm telling you, \Nit's hypothermia. \NHow could it be hypothermia?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:29.55,00:58:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We've all been-- \NMaybe it's just \Nthe flu, you guys.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:31.84,00:58:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, \Nit's not the flu.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:35.30,00:58:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah? \NAnd how do you know?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:37.55,00:58:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Books can be good for \Nsomething other than burning. \NLet's go over her symptoms.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:41.02,00:58:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you. She has a fever \Nand a really cold sweat.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:44.56,00:58:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Woman ] \NHow's her pulse?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:46.73,00:58:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really fast.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:48.61,00:58:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she have any injuries, \Nlike a cut or something \Nthat might have gotten infected?
Dialogue: 0,00:58:52.03,00:58:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,She was complaining \Nabout a cut on her leg \Na few days ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:55.74,00:58:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't-- I didn't \Nthink anything of it.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:03.25,00:59:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my gosh.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:06.29,00:59:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's blood poisoning.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:08.38,00:59:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, septicemia. \NShe could go into septic shock.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:12.05,00:59:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen that before. \NThat can get bad.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:14.30,00:59:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She needs a massive dose \Nof penicillin...
Dialogue: 0,00:59:16.43,00:59:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or a broad-spectrum \Nantibiotic immediately,
Dialogue: 0,00:59:18.72,00:59:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or--
Dialogue: 0,00:59:24.94,00:59:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Or what?
Dialogue: 0,00:59:47.29,00:59:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen \Nanything like it. \NThere's no point of reference.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:50.59,00:59:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All I can see \Nis cloud cover.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:52.46,00:59:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,00:59:54.51,00:59:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking infrared image \Nof thermal currents...
Dialogue: 0,00:59:57.88,01:00:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,sent to Houston, Korolev,
Dialogue: 0,01:00:00.39,01:00:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,your weather service.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:02.43,01:00:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Parker ] \NI'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:05.48,01:00:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom? \NTom, wake up. \N[ Groans ]
Dialogue: 0,01:00:07.60,01:00:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I just received \Nsome satellite images \Nfrom the space station.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:10.48,01:00:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better take a look.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:23.83,01:00:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How big is this thing?
Dialogue: 0,01:00:25.66,01:00:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The vortex is \N50 miles in diameter \Nand growing.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:28.62,01:00:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The two cells \Nover Europe and Asia \Nare even bigger.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:31.13,01:00:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Tom ] \NGood God.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:33.00,01:00:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This one's gonna hit New York \Ninside an hour.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:38.68,01:00:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Gasping, Panting ] \NJack--
Dialogue: 0,01:00:52.11,01:00:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jason!
Dialogue: 0,01:00:54.19,01:00:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,01:00:55.94,01:00:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jason!
Dialogue: 0,01:01:02.53,01:01:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Panting, Gasping ]
Dialogue: 0,01:01:07.37,01:01:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Barking ]
Dialogue: 0,01:01:14.04,01:01:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are you doing? \N- There's gotta be medicine \Non that ship.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:17.55,01:01:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you said \Nit was too dangerous \Nto go outside.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:20.22,01:01:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I did.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:28.52,01:01:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Where'd you find \Nthose chairs?
Dialogue: 0,01:01:42.11,01:01:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Gasps ]
Dialogue: 0,01:02:28.87,01:02:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,01:02:31.50,01:02:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Lock Rattling ] \NOhh! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,01:02:34.17,01:02:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,01:02:36.38,01:02:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Grunts Loudly ] \N- [ Growling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:02:43.34,01:02:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Grunting Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:08.49,01:03:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Yells ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:13.66,01:03:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Panting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:23.92,01:03:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's all in Russian. I-- \N- [ Sam ] I know.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:26.68,01:03:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- H-H-Hey, guys, I found it. \N- What? How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,01:03:30.35,01:03:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it says "penicillin" \Non the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:33.06,01:03:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Growling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:38.19,01:03:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. This is the mess hall. \NWe should find some food \Nwhile we're here.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:42.11,01:03:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have time. \NNone of us are gonna survive \Nwithout food, including Laura.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:47.20,01:03:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:51.03,01:03:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Exhales, Clears Throat ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:53.08,01:03:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[ J.D. ] \NSam, over here!
Dialogue: 0,01:03:55.21,01:03:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,01:03:57.21,01:03:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Bingo. \N[ Laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,01:03:59.38,01:04:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sam Laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,01:04:01.46,01:04:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Glass Clattering ]
Dialogue: 0,01:04:06.34,01:04:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Inflating Loudly ] \N[ Yelling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:04:09.89,01:04:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sam ] \NBrian?
Dialogue: 0,01:04:12.06,01:04:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Brian ] \NI'm okay. \N[ J.D. ] What happened?
Dialogue: 0,01:04:14.77,01:04:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay. All I did \Nwas open up a cupboard.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:18.40,01:04:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Quiet Snarling ] \NWe can use it. \NPut food in it.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:21.61,01:04:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Loud Snarl ] \N[ Gasps ]
Dialogue: 0,01:04:23.48,01:04:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Growling ] \N[ Panicked Yelling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:04:29.78,01:04:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Continues Yelling ] \N- [ Grunting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:04:34.20,01:04:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull him in! \N[ Wolf Whimpers ]
Dialogue: 0,01:04:36.75,01:04:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Whimpering, Growling ] \NYou all right?
Dialogue: 0,01:04:44.09,01:04:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[ J.D. Groans ] \NMy leg.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:49.43,01:04:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, use this.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:50.93,01:04:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shuddering, Groaning ] \NOh, yeah. Here. Ohh!
Dialogue: 0,01:04:59.31,01:05:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be \Nover New York by now.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:01.90,01:05:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Satellite readings \Nare showing a temperature drop \Nof 10 degrees per second.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:22.67,01:05:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Sam ] \NYou guys, I think \Nwe're in the eye of it.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:26.38,01:05:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We gotta get back right now.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:30.63,01:05:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, \NI'm gonna go outside...
Dialogue: 0,01:05:32.55,01:05:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm gonna lure the wolves \Nout of the room.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:35.72,01:05:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- When they leave, \Nyou lock the door. \N- Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:10.26,01:06:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Crunch ] \N- [ Growling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:14.22,01:06:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Yelling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:16.85,01:06:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Aah! \N[ Gasps ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:19.89,01:06:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Muttering, Grunting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:24.48,01:06:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Growling, Snarling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:28.32,01:06:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Aah! \N[ Panting, Gasping ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:36.78,01:06:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- [ Wolf Whimpers ] \N- [ Panting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:43.16,01:06:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Groans ] \NBrian, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,01:06:46.58,01:06:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Muttering ] \NCome on! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,01:06:50.96,01:06:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Snarling, Growling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:53.22,01:06:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Groans, Panting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:06:56.39,01:06:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Growling Continues ] \N[ Banging On Door ]
Dialogue: 0,01:07:00.18,01:07:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Brian! \NBrian, open the door!
Dialogue: 0,01:07:06.90,01:07:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to get out of here now. \NBrian, get the supplies.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:49.65,01:07:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Grunting, Panting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:08:01.16,01:08:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Crackling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:08:08.83,01:08:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,01:08:10.50,01:08:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull! Pull, Brian!
Dialogue: 0,01:08:37.65,01:08:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! Pull!
Dialogue: 0,01:08:48.46,01:08:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the medicine to Laura!
Dialogue: 0,01:08:50.67,01:08:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ J.D. Groaning, Yelling ]
Dialogue: 0,01:09:22.07,01:09:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We're almost there, man! \NCome on! Aah! \N[ Grunts ]
Dialogue: 0,01:09:25.79,01:09:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Brian, close the door!
Dialogue: 0,01:09:40.22,01:09:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let the fire \Ngo out!
Dialogue: 0,01:09:42.59,01:09:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,01:09:50.73,01:09:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha, \Ncome away from the door!
Dialogue: 0,01:09:54.19,01:09:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, Buddha, come!
Dialogue: 0,01:09:55.65,01:09:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,More books! More books!
Dialogue: 0,01:10:52.75,01:10:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How long \Nhave I been out of it?
Dialogue: 0,01:10:55.75,01:10:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Couple hours. \NHow do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,01:10:58.67,01:11:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:00.46,01:11:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,01:11:02.51,01:11:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we had to get inside \Nin kind of a hurry, \Nso I sort of pushed you in.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:08.35,01:11:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I should be used to \Nyou pushing me around.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:11.85,01:11:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to have you back.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:18.73,01:11:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,01:11:21.90,01:11:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The eye of the storm \Nhas passed,
Dialogue: 0,01:11:24.11,01:11:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're 40 miles \Nfrom Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:26.11,01:11:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't we wait \None more day?
Dialogue: 0,01:11:30.87,01:11:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sam may not have \None more day.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:44.78,01:12:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think's \Ngonna happen to us?
Dialogue: 0,01:12:48.70,01:12:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,01:12:51.78,01:12:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean us. \NCivilization.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:54.20,01:12:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:58.29,01:13:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind survived \Nthe last ice age.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:01.33,01:13:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We're certainly capable \Nof surviving this one.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:06.26,01:13:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All depends on \Nwhether or not we're able \Nto learn from our mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:12.22,01:13:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure as hell would like \Na chance to learn from mine.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:16.72,01:13:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You did everything you could.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:22.02,01:13:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking about Sam.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:30.03,01:13:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack, you know \Nthe chances of Sam--
Dialogue: 0,01:13:44.59,01:13:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I made my son a promise.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:48.38,01:13:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to keep it.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:13.36,01:14:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Man On Radio ] \NParker, this is Houston. \NDo you read?
Dialogue: 0,01:14:16.99,01:14:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger, Mission Control. \NGo ahead.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:19.04,01:14:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We're getting scattered reports \Nthat the storm is dissipating \Nover North America.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:23.00,01:14:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you confirm?
Dialogue: 0,01:14:26.63,01:14:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Parker ] \NAffirmative. \NIt's finally clearing.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:31.01,01:14:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We're over Europe right now.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:33.05,01:14:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see landmass \Nfor the first time in days.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:25.12,01:16:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How much further is it \Nto the library?
Dialogue: 0,01:16:27.67,01:16:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be...
Dialogue: 0,01:16:33.05,01:16:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,right here.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:39.51,01:16:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,01:17:18.80,01:17:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sam?
Dialogue: 0,01:18:28.87,01:18:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,01:18:37.75,01:18:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,My father.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:43.51,01:18:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You made it.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:50.02,01:18:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I did.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:17.84,01:19:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Crowd Shouting ]
Dialogue: 0,01:19:31.27,01:19:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Shouting Continues ]
Dialogue: 0,01:19:41.94,01:19:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:46.78,01:19:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I just received \Na shortwave radio transmission \Nfrom Jack Hall.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:50.74,01:19:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He made it to New York.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:53.20,01:19:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He says \Nthere are survivors.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:56.96,01:19:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Tom.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:59.21,01:20:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's--
Dialogue: 0,01:20:02.21,01:20:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good news.
Dialogue: 0,01:20:38.12,01:20:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack! \NIt's good to see you!
Dialogue: 0,01:20:41.54,01:20:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. \NLet's go get on board.
Dialogue: 0,01:21:38.81,01:21:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,01:21:41.23,01:21:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,01:21:43.19,01:21:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever seen the air \Nso clear?
